FunctionalProgramming

1) Fundamental elements used are variables and functions.The data in the functions are immutable(cannot be changed after creation).
2) It follows declarative programming model.
3) It uses recursion for iteration.
4) Does not have any access specifier.


Object Oriented Programming.
1) Fundamental elements used are objects and methods and the data used here are mutable data.
2) Importance is given to data rather than procedures.
3) It follows imperative programming model.
4) It uses loops for iteration.
5) Has three access specifiers namely, Public, Private and Protected.